Sentencas: Spinel structure CuCo2O4 nanoparticles are coated onto porous 10mol% scandia stabilized zirconia (SSZ) framework via a solution impregnation process.
Titulo: Nanostructured CuCo2O4 cathode for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells via an impregnation technique

Sentencas: X-ray diffraction, scanning electron microscopy, electrochemical impedance spectroscopy and current voltage performance measurements have been used to characterize impregnated CuCo2O4 cathodes.
Titulo: Nanostructured CuCo2O4 cathode for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells via an impregnation technique

Sentencas: The CuCo2O4 nano-particles are uniformly distributed on the surface of the porous SSZ backbones, thus increasing the length of the triple phase boundaries (TPBs).
Titulo: Nanostructured CuCo2O4 cathode for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells via an impregnation technique

Sentencas: As expected, the polarization resistance of impregnated nanostructured CuCo2O4 is as low as 0.087 Omega cm(2) in air at 800 degrees C, and delivers a high peak power density of 1136 mW cm(-2).
Titulo: Nanostructured CuCo2O4 cathode for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells via an impregnation technique
